companyProfile.companyDescription: ITC Limited is an India-based diversified conglomerate company. The Company operates in segments, including Fast Moving Consumer Goods (FMCG), Paperboards, Paper and Packaging, and Agri Business. The FMCG segment comprises products such as cigarettes, cigars, education and stationery supplies, personal care items, safety matches, agarbattis, and branded packaged foods, which include staples and meals, snacks, dairy and beverages, biscuits and cakes, chocolates, coffee, and confectionery. The Paperboards, Paper and Packaging segment includes specialty paper and flexible packaging. The Agri Business segment involves the trading of agricultural commodities such as wheat, rice, spices, coffee, soya, and leaf tobacco. Its FMCG brands include Aashirvaad, Sunfeast, Yippee!, Bingo!, B Natural, ITC Master Chef, Fabelle, Sunbean, Fiama, Engage, Vivel, Savlon, Classmate, Paperkraft, Mangaldeep, and others. Its personal care brands feature EDW Essenza, Dermafique, Fiama, Vivel, Engage, and others.

recentNews.headline: For FMCG Inc., the holy grail of volume growth is in sight
recentNews.intro: FMCG companies are shifting focus from price hikes to volume-driven growth due to falling input costs, particularly palm oil. Recent customs duty reductions on edible oils are anticipated to improve profit margins and encourage investment in consumer promotions.
recentNews.imagecaption: Despite selective price hikes by most FMCG companies in recent quarters, these haven't fully offset cost inflation in categories like dairy, beverages, and confectionery.

recentNews.headline: HUL confident of growth in FY26 amid improving demand, lower prices
recentNews.intro: Hindustan Unilever anticipates monetary stimulus, lower inflation, and agricultural growth to drive growth in FY26. The company reported a turnover exceeding  ?60,000 crore for FY25 and a 5% rise in profit.
recentNews.imagecaption: HUL boasts a portfolio of more than 50 brands spanning 15 categories, including packaged foods, home care, and personal care. (Mint)

recentNews.headline: British American Tobacco Offloads $1.5 Billion Stake In ITC Via Block Deal | Share Crashes 4%
recentNews.intro: British American Tobacco (BAT) offloaded a $1.5 billion (approximately  ?12,926 crore) stake in ITC Ltd on Wednesday through a block deal, slightly more than what it had originally planned, according to a term sheet reviewed by Mint. On Tuesday, BAT had announced plans to sell a 2.3% stake in ITC by offloading 290 million shares, valued at about $1.36 billion.
recentNews.imagecaption: British American Tobacco Offloads $1.5 Billion Stake In ITC Via Block Deal

recentNews.headline: Sensex today tumbles 240 points, Nifty slips below 24,800 in choppy trade; ITC top loser
recentNews.intro: Nifty 50 finished the session with a drop of 63 points, or 0.3%, to settle at 24,752, while the Sensex declined 240 points, or 0.29%, to end the day at 81,312. The broader markets managed to buck the trend, as the Nifty Smallcap 100 index gained 0.33%, while the Nifty Midcap 100 index closed flat.
recentNews.imagecaption: Sensex today tumbles 240 points, Nifty slips below 24,800 in choppy trade; ITC top loser
